Sure, here are a few example sentences in Serbian that use the word "prvoj" in different forms and positions:

1. *Prvoj* sam dozvolila da ode. (I allowed the first one to leave.)
2. Volim *prvu* kafu ujutru. (I love the first coffee in the morning.)
3. *Prva* stvar koju uradim kad ustanem je da se istuširam. (The first thing I do when I wake up is take a shower.)
4. Želim da se vidimo *prvom* prilikom. (I want us to meet at the first opportunity.)
5. *Prvom* detetu koje dođe na rođendan, ću dati poklon. (I will give a gift to the first child that comes to the birthday party.)

In these sentences, "prvoj" appears in different forms such as an adjective (*prva*) and an adverb (*prvom*) and in different positions such as at the beginning of the sentence (*prvoj sam dozvolila da ode*) and in the middle of the sentence (*želim da se vidimo prvom prilikom*). 

I hope this helps!